{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b6ff033e-585b-4e19-94a7-c9aefdb45a12","content":"Here's the current state: a bare .NET 10 Web API with two small markdown docs (`configuration.md`, `getting-started.md`) and no dependencies beyond the SDK. Here's the plan:\n\n---\n\n## Architecture — RAG-based Q&A\n\n```\n┌─────────────┐   POST /ingest    ┌──────────────┐    chunk     ┌──────────────┐\n│  Docs/*.md  │ ────────────────► │IngestionSvc  │ ──────────► │  Embed + Store│\n└─────────────┘                   │ (chunk md)   │              │ (VectorStore) │\n                                  └──────────────┘              └──────┬───────┘\n                                                                       │\n┌─────────────┐   POST /ask       ┌──────────────┐   top-K     ┌──────┴───────┐\n│   User Q    │ ────────────────► │  QuerySvc    │ ◄────────── │  VectorStore │\n└─────────────┘                   │              │              └──────────────┘\n                                  │  embed query │\n                                  │  retrieve    │    prompt+   ┌──────────────┐\n                                  │  build prompt│ ──────────► │  LLM (Azure  │\n                                  │  call LLM    │ ◄────────── │  OpenAI)     │\n                                  └──────────────┘   answer    └──────────────┘\n```\n\n### Key components\n\n| Layer | Responsibility | Implementation |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Chunking** | Split each `.md` file into overlapping text chunks (~500 tokens, ~100 token overlap) by markdown headings then sliding window | `Services/DocumentChunker.cs` |\n| **Embedding** | Convert chunks → vectors | Azure OpenAI `text-embedding-3-small` via `Microsoft.Extensions.AI` |\n| **Vector Store** | Persist & search embeddings | In-process `Microsoft.Extensions.VectorData` with an in-memory store (swap to Qdrant/Azure AI Search later) |\n| **Retrieval** | Embed user query → cosine-similarity top-K lookup | `Services/RetrieverService.cs` |\n| **Generation** | Build a grounded prompt (system msg + retrieved chunks + user question) → call chat completion | `Services/AnswerGenerator.cs` |\n| **API surface** | `POST /api/documents/ingest` — ingests all docs; `POST /api/ask` — accepts `{ question }`, returns `{ answer, sources[] }` | `Controllers/DocumentsController.cs`, `Controllers/AskController.cs` |\n\n### NuGet packages to add\n\n- `Microsoft.Extensions.AI.OpenAI` — chat completion + embeddings via the `IChatClient` / `IEmbeddingGenerator` abstractions\n- `Microsoft.Extensions.VectorData.Abstractions` — vector store abstraction\n- `Microsoft.Extensions.VectorData.InMemory` — dev-time in-memory vector DB\n\n### Data model\n\n- **DocumentChunk**: `Id` (GUID), `SourceFile`, `ChunkIndex`, `Text`, `Embedding` (float[])\n- **AskRequest**: `Question` (string)\n- **AskResponse**: `Answer` (string), `Sources` (list of `{ file, chunkText }`)\n\n### Ingestion flow\n\n1. `POST /api/documents/ingest` scans `Docs/*.md`\n2. Each file → `DocumentChunker.Chunk()` → list of text chunks\n3. Each chunk → `IEmbeddingGenerator.GenerateAsync()` → vector\n4. Upsert `DocumentChunk` records into the vector store\n\n### Query flow\n\n1. `POST /api/ask` receives `{ question }`\n2. Embed the question with the same embedding model\n3. Vector similarity search → top 5 chunks\n4. Build prompt: system instruction (\"answer only from provided context\") + retrieved chunks + user question\n5. `IChatClient.GetResponseAsync()` → answer\n6. Return `{ answer, sources }` with the chunk origins\n\n### Configuration\n\nAll keys in `appsettings.json` under an `\"AI\"` section:\n- `Endpoint`, `ApiKey`, `EmbeddingModel`, `ChatModel`, `ChunkSize`, `ChunkOverlap`, `TopK`\n\n### TODOs (in order)\n\n1. Add NuGet package references\n2. Create `Models/` (DTOs + vector-store record)\n3. Create `Services/DocumentChunker.cs`\n4. Create `Services/RetrieverService.cs`\n5. Create `Services/AnswerGenerator.cs`\n6. Register AI services + vector store in `Program.cs`\n7. Create `Controllers/DocumentsController.cs` (`POST /api/documents/ingest`)\n8. Create `Controllers/AskController.cs` (`POST /api/ask`)\n9. Add `appsettings.json` config section\n10. Manually test both endpoints\n\n---\n\nWant me to implement this?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"23ed4210-1614-4f13-921d-dfa71f54887c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I have a clear picture. Let me create a comprehensive plan for the RAG-based Q&A feature.\n\nCurrent state:\n- Minimal .NET 10 Web API (Program.cs with basic setup)\n- Two small markdown docs in `Docs/`\n- No packages beyond the SDK\n\nI'll create a plan covering architecture, components, and todos.","outputTokens":1344},"id":"1e88d0a6-f913-4f46-96b3-57b4d2e08baf","timestamp":"2026-04-08T02:22:27.569Z","parentId":"6d4c6bd4-6309-435d-af06-f096ea4fe266"}
